Which datastructures are enumerated from a DT node

+-------------+       +------------------+       +----------------+       +--------------+
| DT Node     | ----> | platform_device  | ----> | dev structure  | ----> | of_node      |
+-------------+       +------------------+       +----------------+       +--------------+
| - compatible|       | - name           |       | - driver        |       | - name       |
| - reg       |       | - id             |       | - power         |       | - type       |
+-------------+       | - dev            |       | - pm_domain     |       | - properties |
                      +------------------+       | - of_node ------+------>| - parent     |
                                                  +----------------+       +--------------+
DT Node: This is the start, representing the hardware configuration as specified in the device tree source files (.dts).

compatible: Specifies the compatible device or driver.
reg: Hardware address and size used to map the device.
platform_device: Kernel structure representing a platform device.

name, id: Identifiers for the device.
dev: Includes the device structure, linking to more detailed configurations and statuses.
dev: Represents a particular device (part of platform_device).

driver: Links to the device driver handling this device.
power: Power management related data.
pm_domain: Power management domain.
of_node: Points back to the device tree node.
of_node: This is the kernel's internal representation of the DT node.

name, type, properties: Details from the DT.
parent: Points to the parent node in the device tree structure.

